<subSubSection id="C3776556EFDC3AB8FF78F832FB5CFE8E" pageId="141" pageNumber="142" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEFDC3AB8FF78F832FB5CFE8E" blockId="141.[136,778,1839,2070]" lastBlockId="141.[810,1452,173,335]" pageId="141" pageNumber="142">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEFDC3AB8FF78F832FEEFF7D7" bold="true" box="[189,298,2044,2070]" pageId="141" pageNumber="142">Remarks</emphasis>
. In some of the females examined here the dorsal wing-like extension of the first pedigerous somite lacks filiform processes (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EFDC3AB8FB83FF01FB75FF28" box="[1094,1200,207,233]" captionStart="FIGURE 92" captionStartId="140.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[245,1338,207,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-21@140.[204,1383,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="140" captionText="FIGURE 92. Habitus of three species of Notopterophorus. A, female N. auritus (Thorell, 1859), right; B, C, female N. elongatus Buchholz, 1869, right and dorsal; D, E, female N. papilio Hesse, 1864, right and ventral. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591426" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591426/files/figure.png" pageId="141" pageNumber="142">Fig. 92D</figureCitation>
), and the wings of the second pedigerous somite have only posterior filiform processes with the anterior processes either rudimentary (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EFDC3AB8FCF7FEFBFC5DFE8E" box="[818,920,309,335]" captionStart="FIGURE 92" captionStartId="140.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[245,1338,207,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-21@140.[204,1383,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="140" captionText="FIGURE 92. Habitus of three species of Notopterophorus. A, female N. auritus (Thorell, 1859), right; B, C, female N. elongatus Buchholz, 1869, right and dorsal; D, E, female N. papilio Hesse, 1864, right and ventral. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591426" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591426/files/figure.png" pageId="141" pageNumber="142">Fig. 92D</figureCitation>
) or lacking (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EFDC3AB8FBE2FEFBFB48FE8E" box="[1063,1165,309,335]" captionStart="FIGURE 92" captionStartId="140.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[245,1338,207,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-21@140.[204,1383,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="140" captionText="FIGURE 92. Habitus of three species of Notopterophorus. A, female N. auritus (Thorell, 1859), right; B, C, female N. elongatus Buchholz, 1869, right and dorsal; D, E, female N. papilio Hesse, 1864, right and ventral. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591426" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591426/files/figure.png" pageId="141" pageNumber="142">Fig. 92E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
